\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Non-native speakers should note that the word-by-word translations from
 another language like Chinese or German does not work in writing a thesis,
 so students are suggested to always use an English book as a reference
 for language.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Three keywords for scientific writing are 
\shape italic
clarity
\shape default
, 
\shape italic
precision
\shape default
 and 
\shape italic
brevity
\shape default
.
 They can serve as the watchwords to ensure a thesis is readable, persuasive
 and concise.
 Pages 18-26 in 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "cha02"
literal "false"

\end_inset

 provide some very useful hints on understanding the three words and discusses
 some other issues on the use of language in thesis writing.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
An important stylistic choice in scientific writing is between active voice
 and passive voice.
 One way to express what was done is to e.g.
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

say 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

I performed frequency measurements
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

.
 In this way it becomes obvious what was done by the author.
 However, this kind of writing is uncommon in scientific work and should
 be used only when there would be uncertainties about who contributed which
 pieces of work.
 A better alternative writing to make this obvious is use a sentence similar
 to 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Frequency measurements were conducted by the author
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

.
 In most situations a passive form like 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Frequency measurements were conducted
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 is the best option.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In a scientific thesis it is very unusual to address the reader directly
 as 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

you
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

.
 Thus, one should change sentences like 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

This chapter tells you the reason why ...
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 to 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

This chapter gives reasons why ...
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

